The scientific literature has no answers to the question of the origin of the immune system.” (Darwin’s Black Box, p. 138)--(PvM: Note how these are the typical ID arguments against science, we do not know, thus designed) As the debate over “irreducible complexity” developed in the next decade, the most detailed arguments would go basically like this: ID: Gradual evolution by natural selection can’t produce IC structures because any structure missing a part would be nonfunctional Evo: You are ignoring cooption of structures with different functions, which has a been a major feature of the evolutionary explanation of complex structures ever since the Origin of Species.
